> This is what happened in March 1989 in the Canadian province of Quebec, when the power grid lost power. The culprit? A solar storm.

In fact, Canada saw the effect of solar storms on two occasions that year. A summary of the effect of the March 1989 solar storm can be found on [NASA's website](https://www.nasa.gov/topics/earth/features/sun_darkness.html). A second [solar storm](https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg12316812.400-solar-storms-halt-stock-market-as-computers-crash/
) is believed to have been responsible for the halt of the stock market in Toronto a few months later.
